## 4. Notable IEEE 802.3 Ethernet Standards

The physical network layer formats use standard designations indicating transmission speed, signaling method, and physical medium type:

* **1000BASE-T:** Gigabit speed over Twisted-Pair Copper (Cat 5e/6 implementations) spanning a 100m limits.
* **10GBASE-T:** 10 Gigabit data over Twisted-Pair Copper (Cat 6 up to 55m, Cat 6A extending to 100m).
* **10GBASE-SR:** 10 Gigabit Short-Range over Multi-Mode Fiber (typically matching 300m bounds).
* **10GBASE-LR:** 10 Gigabit Long-Range over Single-Mode Fiber (engineered to cover up to 10km lengths).

